node.text:
Based on a threat-informed, ten-year time horizon, the Marine Corps is designing a force for naval expeditionary warfare in actively contested spaces. Throughout this ten-year initiative, the Marine Corps will make investments in capabilities to include long range precision fires, advanced reconnaissance capabilities, unmanned systems, and resilient networks. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Nicholas Filca)

For more information, view the link in the bio.

node.text:
Duck, Duck...

Capt. Austin Bentley, an F/A-18 Hornet pilot with Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA) 232, @3rdmaw, walks on the flight line at Andersen Air Force Base, Guam, during Pacific Iron 2021. 

Pacific Iron 2021 focuses on deploying, operating, and sustaining forces from smaller dispersed bases in the #FreeAndOpenIndoPacific region. 

#Pilot #PacificIron2021 

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Tyler Harmon)

node.text:
Semper Fi-nance

Today is National Financial Awareness Day. Marines fight and win in every clime and place, and that includes the world of personal finance. Take time today to review your financial combat power. Reach out to your installation @mccs_hq Personal Financial Management Specialists for access to financial counseling and planning resources.

#Marines #USMC #FinancialFreedom #PersonalFinance #USMCFamily #MilFamily

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on August 14, 2021.

node.text:
#Marines depart the #USSSanDiego on a Landing Craft Air Cushion for a ship-to-shore movement during Large Scale Exercise 2021. 

Wargames such as #LSE21 increase @usnavy and Marine Corps interoperability as a globally integrated Naval Force capable of projecting American power from sea to shore at home and around the world.

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by @3dmardiv 2nd Lt. Erin E. Scudder)

node.text:
On #NavajoCodeTalkersDay, we honor the Navajo Nation Marines that served on every battleground of the Pacific during WWII, and whose spoken code was never broken. Semper Fidelis. 

#Marines #USMC #USMCHistory

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on August 13, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Sgt. Mario Oliva Sanchez, a Joint Terminal Attack Controller with @3dmardiv, calls for close air support during Large Scale Exercise 2021 at @mcb_hawaii.  #LSE21 connects high-fidelity training and real-world operations to build knowledge and skills needed in today’s complex, multi-domain, and contested environment.

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by Sgt. Josue Marquez)

node.text:
#OTD in 1918, Opha May Johnson became the first woman to be sworn in the Marine Corps. She, along with her 304 other colleagues, pioneered the way for generations of women who have earned the lifelong title of Marine. Semper Fidelis. 

#Marines #USMC #USMCHistory #TheFewTheProud

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
Offensive Operations ☠️

Lance Cpl. Gavin Wright, a rifleman with @3dmardiv, conducts offensive operations on key maritime terrain during Large Scale Exercise 2021 on @mcb_hawaii. 

#LSE21 is based on a progression of scenarios that will assess and refine modern warfare concepts, including Distributed Maritime Operations (DMO), Expeditionary Advanced Base Operations (EABO), and Littoral Operations in a Contested Environment (LOCE). 

LSE 2021 is the first iteration of what will become a triennial exercise with plans for future iterations to include partners and allies from around the world. 

#Maritime #JointForce #USMC 

(U.S. Marine Corps photos by Cpl. Alexis Moradian)

Any Clime, Any Place

A drill instructor with Bravo Company, 1st Recruit Training Battalion, watches his recruits execute drill movements aboard @mcrdparrisisland.

⚔️⚔️ Close order drill helps to instill self-discipline in recruits as they become U.S. #Marines. 

#DrillInstructor #ParrisIsland 

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Ryan Hageali)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United States Marine Corps in Saudi Arabia. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Snap, Pop 💥

A Marine with assigned to @spmagtf_cr_cc fires an M4 service rifle at a target during a Combat Marksmanship Program range in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. 

The CMP range allows Marines to maintain rifle proficiency while being put through various courses of fire. 

The SPMAGTF-CR-CC is a crisis response force, prepared to deploy a variety of capabilities across the region. 🌍

#Rifle #SaudiArabia

(U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Willow Marshall)

node.text:
One Shot, One Kill

A Low Altitude Air Defense Basic Gunner Course student assigned to the Air Control Training Squadron, Marine Corps Communications-Electronics School fires an FIM-92 Stinger missile at @thecombatcenter.

LAAD students were certified to fire the FIM-92 Stinger missile during the exercise, a graduation prerequisite before moving to the Fleet Marine Force. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Lance Cpl. Colton Brownlee)

#Gunner #Missile
